Mix 1 NCState PCA

library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)
library(RcppCNPy)
library(ggrepel)
C <- as.matrix(read.table("data/trout_mix1_WGS_NCState_run2.cov"))
metadata <- read_csv("data/trout_mix_1_metadata.csv")
New names:Rows: 99 Columns: 48── Column specification ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: ","
chr (24): NMFS_DNA_ID...1, BOX_ID, BOX_POSITION, SAMPLE_ID, BATCH_ID, GENU...
dbl  (4): LENGTH, WEIGHT, LATITUDE_F, LONGITUDE_F
lgl (20): PROJECT_NAME, AGE, PHENOTYPE, HATCHERY_MARK, TAG_NUMBER, ESTIMAT...
ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
e <- eigen(C)
t <- tibble(PC1 = e$vectors[,1],
            PC2 = e$vectors[,2])
units <- read_tsv("data/units-2ndrun.tsv")
Rows: 98 Columns: 12── Column specification ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Delimiter: "\t"
chr (8): sample, library, flowcell, platform, sample_id, barcode, fq1, fq2
dbl (4): unit, lane, kb1, kb2
ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
sample_id <- units$sample
temp <- add_column(t, sample_id)
data <- left_join(temp, metadata, by = c("sample_id" = "NMFS_DNA_ID...1"))
wn_colors <- c( `Mulkey Creek` = "deepskyblue3",
                `Fish Creek` = "deeppink3",
                `Lion Creek` = "firebrick3",
                `Tamarack Creek` = "lightpink3",
                `North Fork Clicks Creek` = "orange3",
                `Deadman Creek` = "olivedrab3",
                `Nacimiento River` = "seagreen3",
                `San Lorenzo River` = "thistle3")
county_shapes <- c( `Tulare` = 22,
                    `Monterey` = 24,
                    `Santa Cruz` = 25)

ggplot(data = data,
       mapping = aes( x = PC1,
                      y = PC2,
                      shape = COUNTY_F,
                      fill = WATER_NAME)) +
  geom_point(size = 4.5) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) +
  geom_point(size = 5,
             stroke = 0.05,
             alpha = 0.75) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = wn_colors) +
  scale_shape_manual(values = county_shapes) +
  guides(fill = guide_legend(override.aes = list(shape = 22,
                                                 stroke = 0.5,
                                                 size = 3)),
         shape = guide_legend(override.aes = list(stroke = 0.5,
                                                  size = 3))) +
  labs(shape = "County",
       fill = "Water Name") +
  geom_text_repel(aes(label = data$sample_id),
                      max.overlaps = 50)
